'''Adult lifetime cannabis use by country''' is the lifetime prevalence of [[Cannabis (drug)|cannabis]] use among all adults in surveys among the general population.<ref name=EMCDDA>[http://www.emcdda.europa.eu/html.cfm/index39559EN.html Table GPS-8 Part (i) "Lifetime prevalence of drug use among all adults (aged 15 to 64 years old) in nationwide surveys among the general population"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080409192228/http://www.emcdda.europa.eu/html.cfm/index39559EN.html |date=2008-04-09 }}. Statistical bulletin 2007 (archive), EMCDDA ([[European Monitoring Centre for Drugs and Drug Addiction]]).</ref><ref name="plos2008july">[http://journals.plos.org/plosmedicine/article?id=10.1371/journal.pmed.0050141 "Toward a Global View of Alcohol, Tobacco, Cannabis, and Cocaine Use: Findings from the WHO World Mental Health Surveys"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180112042450/http://journals.plos.org/plosmedicine/article?id=10.1371%2Fjournal.pmed.0050141 |date=2018-01-12 }} July 2008, Volume 5, Issue 7, e141. ''[[PLoS Medicine]]'' ([[Public Library of Science]]). In the '''[http://www.libre-ou-pas.fr/2017/03/10/la-dependance-au-cannabis/ full article]{{dead link|date=March 2018|bot=medic}}{{cbignore|bot=medic}}''' see Table 1 for the survey dates, and participant ages. See '''Table 2''' for the '''percentages of use by country.'''</ref> Lifetime prevalence means any use of cannabis during a person’s life.<ref name=methods>[http://www.emcdda.europa.eu/stats07/GPS/methods Methods and definitions] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090202153516/http://www.emcdda.europa.eu/stats07/GPS/methods |date=2009-02-02 }}. [[EMCDDA]].</ref> Unless another reference is indicated (see "References" column) all the data comes from the [[European Monitoring Centre for Drugs and Drug Addiction]]s statistical bulletin from 2007.<ref name=EMCDDA/>
