{{Infobox waterfall | name = Coon Creek Falls | photo = Coon Creek Falls.jpg | photo_width = 250 | photo_caption = Coon Creek Falls | location = [[Spencer, Tennessee|Spencer]], [[Tennessee]], [[United States]] | coords = {{Coord|35.66642|-85.35655|region:US_type:waterbody|display=inline,title}} | elevation = | type = Plunge | height = {{convert|250|ft|m}} | width = | height_longest = | average_width = | number_drops = | average_flow = | watercourse = Coon Creek | world_rank = }} '''Coon Creek Falls''', is a {{convert|250|ft|m}} plunge waterfall which shares a plungepool with [[Fall Creek Falls]]. The falls are not always present, depending on the amount of precipitation in the area. The falls are located near Spencer, Tennessee in [[Fall Creek Falls State Park]].<ref>{{cite book|last=Manning|first=Russ|title=40 Hikes in Tennessee's South Cumberland|year=2000|publisher=Mountaineers|location=Seattle, WA|isbn=978-0-89886-637-7|pages=83|edition=3rd}}</ref>
