'''Still Brook Waterfall''' is a [[waterfall]] at mouth of Still Brook,<ref>{{cite web
 | url = https://gis8.nsgc.gov.ns.ca/scripts/esrimap.dll?name=nsplacenames&cmd=4&zoomcons=1&action=zoomToPlace&title=Still%20Brook&objid=58159&prov=false
 | title = Nova Scotia Geographical Names Database entry for "Still Brook, Victoria County" (includes map)
 | publisher = Government of Nova Scotia
 | accessdate = May 10, 2012
}}</ref> where the brook empties into Black Brook Cove, and so into the [[Atlantic Ocean]].  Still Brook Waterfall flows onto Black Brook Beach, a popular swimming and picnic site on the [[Cabot Trail]] in the [[Cape Breton Highlands National Park]], {{convert|10|km|mi|0}} north of [[Ingonish, Nova Scotia | Ingonish]], [[Nova Scotia]], [[Canada]]. 
