The following is a timeline of the [[History of Tokyo|history]] of [[Tokyo]], [[Japan]]. {{Dynamic list}} {{TOC right}}
==Prior to 19th century== {{History of Japan}}
* 1457 - [[Edo Castle]] built.{{sfn|Cybriwsky|2011|ps=: "Chronology"|page=xvii}} * 1617 - [[Yoshiwara]] (prostitution district) begins operating.{{sfn|Mansfield|2009}} * 1634 - [[Sankin-kōtai]] policy established.{{sfn|Guth|1996}} * 1657 - March 2: [[Great Fire of Meireki]] occurs.<ref name=MetroCalendar /> * 1682 - {{Interlanguage link multi|1682 Edo fire|ja|3=天和の大火}}.{{sfn|Meech|2008}} * 1698 - {{Interlanguage link multi|1698 Edo fire|ja|3=勅額火事}}.{{sfn|Meech|2008}} * 1707 - December: [[Hōei eruption of Mount Fuji|Eruption of Mount Fuji]]; ash falls on Edo.{{sfn|Meech|2008}} * 1721 - "First population census conducted (Edo’s population about 1.3 million)."<ref name=MetroCalendar />
==19th century==
* 1853 ** July 8: American [[Perry Expedition]] arrives in Edo Bay. ** [[Odaiba]] island forts built in Edo Bay. ** [[Hanayashiki]] garden opens.{{sfn|Mansfield|2009}} * 1855 - November 11: [[1855 Edo earthquake]] occurs. * 1856 - Hiroshige's ''[[One Hundred Famous Views of Edo]]'' published. * 1868 - Edo renamed "Tokyo."<ref name=MetroCalendar>{{cite web |title=Historical Calendar of Tokyo |url=http://www.metro.tokyo.jp/ENGLISH/ABOUT/APPENDIX/appendix01.htm |publisher= Tokyo Metropolitan Government |accessdate=July 30, 2015 }} (timeline)</ref> * 1869 ** Japanese [[Empire of Japan|imperial]] capital relocated to Tokyo from [[Kyoto]].<ref name=JapanSociety-religion /> ** [[Yasukuni Shrine|Tokyo Shôkonsha]] (shrine) established.<ref name=JapanSociety-religion /> ** Yokohama-Tokyo telegraph begins operating.<ref name=JapanSociety-Modern>{{cite web |publisher=[[Japan Society (Manhattan)|Japan Society]] |location=New York |url=http://aboutjapan.japansociety.org/content.cfm/timeline_modern |title= Timeline of Modern Japan (1868-1945) |work= About Japan: a Teacher’s Resource }}</ref> * 1871 - [[Esaki Reiji]] photo studio in business.<ref name=houston2003-timeline>{{cite book|title=History of Japanese Photography|year=2003|publisher=[[Museum of Fine Arts, Houston]] |location=USA |isbn=978-0-300-09925-6 |chapter=Chronology |chapterurl= https://books.google.com/books?id=gQkHWBEbFxIC&pg=PT339 }}</ref> * 1872 ** October: Yokohama-Tokyo railroad begins operating.{{sfn|Freedman|2011}} ** ''[[Tokyo Nichi Nichi Shimbun]]'' (newspaper) begins publication. ** "Ordinances aimed at the civilizing of the populace are enacted in Tokyo."<ref name=JapanSociety-Modern /> ** [[Imperial Library (Japan)|Imperial Library]] headquartered in Tokyo.<ref name=nccjapan /> * 1873 - [[Dai-Ichi Kokuritsu Bank]] established.<ref name="Tamaki1995">{{cite book|author= Norio Tamaki |title=Japanese Banking: A History, 1859-1959|chapter=Genealogy of leading Japanese banks, 1859-1959 |chapterurl=https://books.google.com/books?id=jJZVJz1YMzMC&pg=PR18 |year= 1995|publisher=Cambridge University Press|isbn=978-0-521-02233-0}}</ref> * 1874 - [[Aoyama Gakuin University|Aoyama Gakuin]] school and [[Rikkyo University|Saint Paul's]] school established.<ref name=JapanSociety-religion /> * 1877 ** [[University of Tokyo]]<ref name=JapanSociety-Modern /> and {{Interlanguage link multi|Fifteen Bank|ja|3=十五銀行}}<ref name="Tamaki1995" /> established. ** {{Interlanguage link multi|National Industrial Exhibition|ja|3=内国勧業博覧会}} held.<ref name=expositions2011>{{cite web |url=http://www.ndl.go.jp/exposition/e/s1/index.html |title=Expositions: where the modern technology of the times was exhibited |publisher=[[National Diet Library]] |location=Tokyo |year=2011 }}</ref> * 1880 - [[Mitsubishi Bank]] and [[Fuji Bank|Yasuda Bank]] established.<ref name=davies2002>{{cite web |url= http://projects.exeter.ac.uk/RDavies/arian/amser/chrono.html |title=Comparative Chronology of Money |author1= [[Glyn Davies (economist)|Glyn Davies]] |author2= Roy Davies |year=2002 |via=University of Exeter }}</ref> * 1881 ** [[Tokyo National Museum|Tokyo Imperial Museum]] built.<ref name=MMA-eaj10>{{cite web |url= http://www.metmuseum.org/toah/ht/?period=10&region=eaj#/Key-Events |title= Japan, 1800–1900 A.D.: Key Events |work= Heilbrunn Timeline of Art History |publisher=[[Metropolitan Museum of Art]] |location=New York |accessdate=July 30, 2015 }}</ref> ** [[Tokyo Institute of Technology|Tokyo Vocational School]] founded. * 1882 ** [[Bank of Japan]] headquartered in city.<ref name="Tamaki1995" /> ** [[Ueno Zoo]] opens.<ref name="Kisling2000">{{cite book|editor=Vernon N. Kisling|title=Zoo and Aquarium History|year= 2000|publisher=[[CRC Press]] |location=USA |isbn=978-1-4200-3924-5 |chapter=Zoological Gardens of Japan (chronological list) |chapterurl= https://books.google.com/books?id=dxTrR5nOE0UC&pg=PA384 }}</ref> * 1884 - Railway [[Yamanote Line]] begins operating.{{sfn|Freedman|2011}} * 1886 - "First fixed advertising billboard in Tokyo" installed.<ref name=moeran1996>{{cite book|author= Brian Moeran |title=A Japanese Advertising Agency: An Anthropology of Media and Markets |isbn=978-1-136-79533-6 |chapter=Chronology of Japanese Advertising and Media from 1862 to 1991 |chapterurl= https://books.google.com/books?id=Za7dAAAAQBAJ&pg=PA298 |publisher= University of Hawaii Press |year=1996 }}</ref> * 1887 - {{Interlanguage link multi|Tokyo School of Art|ja|3=東京美術学校 (旧制)}} founded.<ref name=JapanSociety-Modern /> * 1888 ** ''[[Asahi Shimbun|Tokyo Asahi Shimbun]]'' (newspaper) begins publication. ** {{Interlanguage link multi|Tokyo Observatory|ja|3=東京天文台}} established. * 1889 ** "Tokyo City and 15 wards established."<ref name=MetroCalendar /> ** [[Kabuki-za]] (theatre) opens.{{sfn|Mansfield|2009}} * 1890 ** Telephone begins operating.<ref name=JapanSociety-Modern /> ** Population: 1,155,290.<ref name=okasaki1957>{{cite journal |title=Growth of Urban Population in Japan |author= Ayanori Okasaki |journal= Genus |volume= 13 |year=1957 |jstor= 29787368}}</ref> * 1894 - Tokyo-fu Government Building constructed in [[Marunouchi]].<ref name=MetroCalendar /> * 1897 - March: Motion picture first shown.<ref name=Sharp2011-chronology>{{cite book|author=Jasper Sharp|title=Historical Dictionary of Japanese Cinema|year=2011|publisher=[[Scarecrow Press]]|isbn=978-0-8108-7541-8 |chapter=Chronology |chapterurl= https://books.google.com/books?id=oAYsyZRRqzcC&pg=PR19 }}</ref>
==20th century==
===1900s-1940s=== * 1901 - Tokyo Photography Circle (club) formed.<ref name=houston2003-timeline /> * 1902 - [[Industrial Bank of Japan]] headquartered in city.<ref name="Tamaki1995" /> * 1903 ** Electric tram begins operating.<ref name=Henshall2014-timeline>{{cite book|author=Kenneth Henshall|title=Historical Dictionary of Japan to 1945 |year=2014|publisher=[[Scarecrow Press]] |location=USA |isbn=978-0-8108-7872-3 |chapter=Chronology |chapterurl= https://books.google.com/books?id=tmYYAgAAQBAJ&pg=PR15}}</ref> ** Electric Hall (cinema) opens.{{sfn|Mansfield|2009}} * 1905 - September 5: [[Hibiya Incendiary Incident]] occurs.{{sfn|Cybriwsky|2011|ps=: "Chronology"|page=xvii}} * 1906 - [[Harajuku Station]] opens. * 1907 - Tokyo Industrial Exhibition held.<ref name=expositions2011 /> * 1910 - [[Luna Park, Tokyo|Luna Park]] opens. * 1911 - [[Imperial Theatre (Japan)|Imperial Theatre]] opens.<ref name=CinemaTreasures /> * 1914 ** December: [[Tokyo Station|Central Station]] opens.{{sfn|Freedman|2011}} ** Taisho Exposition held.<ref name=JapanSociety-Modern /> * 1916 - Tokyo Photographers Guild established.<ref name=houston2003-timeline /> * 1917 - {{Interlanguage link multi|Asakusa Opera|ja|3=浅草オペラ}} active.<ref name="Mitsui2014">{{cite book|editor= Toru Mitsui |title=Made in Japan: Studies in Popular Music|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=YWQKBAAAQBAJ|year= 2014|publisher=Routledge|isbn=978-1-135-95534-2}}</ref> * 1918 ** [[Rice riots of 1918|Rice riot]] occurs.<ref name=JapanSociety-Modern /> ** Neon light installed in [[Ginza]].<ref name=moeran1996 /> * 1920 ** [[Meiji Shrine]] built.<ref name=JapanSociety-religion>{{cite web |publisher=[[Japan Society (Manhattan)|Japan Society]] |location=New York |url=http://aboutjapan.japansociety.org/content.cfm/timeline_of_religion_and_nationalism |title= Timeline of Religion and Nationalism in Meiji and Imperial Japan |work= About Japan: a Teacher’s Resource |accessdate=July 30, 2015 }}</ref> ** Population: 3,699,428.<ref name=MetroCalendar /> * 1921 - November 4: Japanese prime minister [[Takashi Hara]] assassinated.{{sfn|Cybriwsky|2011|ps=: "Chronology"|page=xvii}} * 1923 - September 1: [[1923 Great Kantō earthquake]] occurs.<ref name=bbcTimeline>{{cite web |url= https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-pacific-15219730 |author=BBC News |title=Japan Profile: Timeline |accessdate=July 30, 2015}}</ref> * 1925 - {{Interlanguage link multi|Tokyo Broadcasting Station|ja|3=東京放送局}} begins operating.<ref name="Sugimoto2009">{{cite book|editor= Yoshio Sugimoto |title=Cambridge Companion to Modern Japanese Culture|year= 2009|publisher=Cambridge University Press|isbn=978-1-107-49546-3 |chapter=Chronology |chapterurl= https://books.google.com/books?id=s80AAwAAQBAJ&pg=PT15 }}</ref><ref name=Sharp2011-chronology /> * 1926 ** "Public apartment housing" built.<ref name=JapanSociety-Modern /> ** [[NHK Symphony Orchestra]]<ref name=Lawson2003-20th>{{cite book|editor= [[Colin Lawson]] |title= Cambridge Companion to the Orchestra|year= 2003|publisher=Cambridge University Press|isbn=978-0-521-00132-8 |chapter= Orchestras Founded in the 20th Century (chronological list) |chapterurl= https://books.google.com/books?id=1DW1WyiooSMC&pg=PA277 }}</ref> and [[Tokyo Metropolitan Art Museum]] established. * 1927 - [[Tokyo Metro Ginza Line|Tokyo Underground Railway]] begins operating between [[Asakusa]] and [[Ueno]].<ref name=JapanSociety-Modern /> * 1928 - {{Interlanguage link multi|Daiba Park|ja|3=台場公園}} opens in Tokyo Bay. * 1929 - ''[[Tokyo March]]'' song/film become popular.<ref name="Miyao2013">{{cite book|editor=Daisuke Miyao|title= Oxford Handbook of Japanese Cinema|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=XXD1AQAAQBAJ|year= 2013|publisher=Oxford University Press |isbn=978-0-19-973166-4}}</ref> * 1930 - Population: 4,986,913.<ref name=okasaki1957 /> * 1931 - [[Haneda Airport]] begins operating.<ref name=MetroCalendar /> * 1933 - [[DN Tower 21|Dai-Ichi Seimei Building]] constructed. * 1934 ** [[Yomiuri Giants]] baseball team formed.{{sfn|Cybriwsky|2011}} ** {{Interlanguage link multi|Hibiya Theatre|ja|3=日比谷映画}} opens.<ref name=CinemaTreasures /> * 1936 ** [[Konica|Konishiroku Honten]] in business.<ref>{{citation |url=http://www.konicaminolta.com/about/corporate/history_timeline.html |publisher=Konica Minolta |title= History Timeline |accessdate=July 30, 2015 }}</ref> ** [[Japanese Folk Crafts Museum]] founded.<ref name=MMA-eaj11>{{cite web |url= http://www.metmuseum.org/toah/ht/?period=11&region=eaj#/Key-Events |title= Japan, 1900 A.D.-present: Key Events |work= Heilbrunn Timeline of Art History |publisher=[[Metropolitan Museum of Art]] |location=New York |accessdate=July 30, 2015 }}</ref> * 1937 - [[Korakuen Stadium]] opens.{{sfn|Cybriwsky|2011}} * 1938 - [[Rikugi-en]] (park) opens. * 1940 - Population: 6,778,804.<ref name=okasaki1957 /> * 1941 - [[Port of Tokyo]] opens.<ref name=MetroCalendar /> * 1942 - April: [[Bombing of Tokyo]] by US forces begins. * 1943 - "Metropolitan administration system established."<ref name=MetroCalendar /> * 1945 ** 10 March: [[Bombing of Tokyo (10 March 1945)|A major air attack]] kills 90,000 to 100,000 people and destroys a quarter of the city's buildings ** August: [[Bombing of Tokyo]] by US forces ends. ** {{Interlanguage link multi|Japan Savings Bank|ja|3=日本貯蓄銀行}} established.<ref name="Tamaki1995" /> ** Population: 3,488,284.<ref name=UN1955>{{cite web |url= https://unstats.un.org/unsd/demographic/products/dyb/1950_round.htm |work=Demographic Yearbook 1955 |year= |publisher=[[Statistical Office of the United Nations]] |location=New York |title=Population of capital city and cities of 100,000 or more inhabitants }}</ref> * 1946 - [[Tokyo War Crimes Tribunal]] begins.<ref name="Sugimoto2009" /> * 1947 ** {{illm|Seiichirō Yasui|fr|Seiichirō Yasui|ja|安井誠一郎}} elected governor.<ref name=MetroCalendar /> ** 23 [[Special wards of Tokyo]] created.<ref name=MetroCalendar /> * 1948 - [[National Diet Library]] headquartered in Tokyo.<ref name=nccjapan />
===1950s-1990s=== * 1950 - Population: 6,277,500.<ref name=UN1955 /> * 1955 ** Tokyo International Trade Fair begins.<ref name=moma2012>{{cite book |publisher=[[Museum of Modern Art]] |location=New York |title=Tokyo, 1955-1970: a New Avant-garde |year=2012 |isbn=978-0-87070-834-3 |chapter=Chronology |chapterurl=https://books.google.com/books?id=oGeO8euGgTkC&pg=PA180 }}</ref> ** Population: 6,966,499.<ref name=okasaki1957 /> * 1958 ** [[National Olympic Stadium (Tokyo)|Japanese National Stadium]] opens. ** May: [[1958 Asian Games]] held in Tokyo. * 1961 ** {{Interlanguage link multi|Suntory Art Museum|ja|3=サントリー美術館}} opens. ** Higashi-Ikebukuro Taishôken ramen shop in business.<ref name=ramen2015>{{citation |date=January 2015 |work=[[Lucky Peach]] |title=Timeline of Ramen Development |url=http://luckypeach.com/a-timeline-of-ramen-development }}</ref> * 1964 ** [[Tōkaidō Shinkansen]] (hi-speed train) begins operating;<ref name="Hood2006">{{cite book|author=Christopher P. Hood|title=Shinkansen: From Bullet Train to Symbol of Modern Japan |year=2006|publisher=Routledge|isbn=978-1-134-36089-5 |chapter=Chronology |chapterurl=https://books.google.com/books?id=cwbklrvmS-oC&pg=PA211 }}</ref> ** October: [[1964 Summer Olympics]] held in Tokyo.<ref name=bbcTimeline /> ** [[Tokyo 12 Channel TV]] begins broadcasting.<ref name=moeran1996 /> ** [[Hotel New Otani Tokyo]] built. * 1967 - [[Yoyogi Park]] created. * 1968 ** [[Kasumigaseki Building]] (hi-rise) built. ** [[Ramen Jiro]] eatery in business.<ref name=ramen2015 /> * 1969 - "{{Interlanguage link multi|Tokyo Metropolitan Pollution Control Ordinance|ja|3=東京都公害防止条例}} enacted."<ref name=MetroCalendar /> * 1971 - [[Keio Plaza Hotel]] (hi-rise) built. * 1972 - [[Nakagin Capsule Tower]] built. * 1973 - [[Tokyo Metropolitan Library]] opens.<ref name=nccjapan>{{cite web |url=http://guides.nccjapan.org/content.php?pid=338268&sid=5485626 |title= Institutions in Japan: Browse by Region (Kinki) |work=Research Access in Japanese Museums, Libraries, and Archives Resources |publisher=North American Coordinating Council on Japanese Library Resources |accessdate=July 30, 2015 }}</ref> * 1975 ** Ward mayoral election held.<ref name=MetroCalendar /> ** Population: 8,640,000 city; 11,622,651 urban agglomeration.<ref>{{cite book |url= https://unstats.un.org/unsd/demographic/products/dyb/1970_round.htm |title=Demographic Yearbook 1975 |year=1976 |author=[[United Nations Department of Economic and Social Affairs]], Statistical Office |location=New York |chapter=Population of capital city and cities of 100,000 and more inhabitants |pages=253-279 }}</ref> * 1979 - June: [[5th G7 summit]] held in city. * 1988 ** [[Tokyo Dome]] (stadium) opens.{{sfn|Cybriwsky|2011}} ** [[Yumenoshima Tropical Greenhouse Dome]] established.<ref name=botanic>{{cite web |url= http://www.bgci.org/garden_search.php?action=Find&ftrCountry=JP |title=Garden Search: Japan |publisher= [[Botanic Gardens Conservation International]] |location=London |accessdate=July 30, 2015 }}</ref> * 1989 - [[Bunkamura]] cultural venue opens. * 1991 - Metropolitan government relocates to [[Tokyo Metropolitan Government Building|new building]] in Shinjuku.<ref name=MetroCalendar /> * 1993 ** [[Rainbow Bridge (Tokyo)|Rainbow Bridge]] opens.<ref name=MetroCalendar /> ** [[DN Tower 21]] built. * 1995 - March 20: [[Tokyo subway sarin attack]].<ref name=bbcTimeline /> * 1996 - [[Tokyo Big Sight]] convention centre opens. * 2000 - Population: 8,130,408.<ref name="europa2004">{{cite book|title=Europa World Year Book |year=2004|publisher=[[Europa Publications]] |isbn=978-1-85743-254-1 |chapter=Japan |chapterurl= https://books.google.com/books?id=wGA4o-UhAfgC&pg=PA2341 }}</ref>
==21st century==
* 2001 - October: [[Asian Network of Major Cities 21]] meets in Tokyo.<ref name=MetroCalendar /> * 2002 - [[Tokyo International Anime Fair]] begins. * 2004 - {{Interlanguage link multi|ShinGinkō Tokyo|ja|3=新銀行東京}} bank established.<ref name=MetroCalendar /> * 2005 - [[Tokyo Metropolitan University]] established.<ref name=MetroCalendar /> * 2007 ** [[Tokyo Marathon]] begins.<ref name=MetroCalendar /> ** [[Midtown Tower]] built. ** Shinjuku Wald 9 cinema in business.<ref name=CinemaTreasures>{{cite web |url= http://cinematreasures.org/theaters/japan/tokyo?status=all |title=Movie Theaters in Tokyo |work=CinemaTreasures.org |publisher= Cinema Treasures LLC |location=Los Angeles |accessdate=July 30, 2015 }}</ref> * 2008 - [[C40 Cities Climate Leadership Group|C40]] environmental group meets in Tokyo.<ref name=MetroCalendar /> * 2011 - [[2011 Tōhoku earthquake and tsunami|2011 Tōhoku earthquake]] occurs.<ref name=MetroCalendar /> * 2012 ** [[Tokyo Gate Bridge]] opens.<ref name=MetroCalendar /> ** [[Tokyo Skytree]] tower built.<ref name=MetroCalendar /> * 2013 - September: Tokyo chosen as site of the future [[2020 Summer Olympics]].<ref name=bbcTimeline /> * 2014 ** [[Toranomon Hills]] (hi-rise) built. ** [[Yoichi Masuzoe]] elected [[Tokyo_Metropolitan_Government#Governor|governor]].<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.citymayors.com/mayors/japanese-mayors.html |title=Japanese Mayors |location=London |work=City Mayors.com |publisher=[[City Mayors Foundation]] |accessdate=July 30, 2015 }}</ref> * 2016 - [[Yuriko Koike]] elected governor.<ref>{{citation |work=BBC News |title=Tokyo elects Yuriko Koike as first female governor |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-asia-36935083 |date=1 August 2016 }}</ref>
