'''Trešnjevka''' is a large neighbourhood in the western part of the city of [[Zagreb]], [[Croatia]].
[[File:Trešnjevka Remiza aerial.jpg|right|thumb|Aerial view of the [[Zagreb tram]] depot at Ljubljanica, Trešnjevka]]
It is administratively divided into two districts: * [[Trešnjevka - sjever]] (''Trešnjevka - north'')<ref>[[City of Zagreb]], [http://www.zagreb.hr/default.aspx?id=155 Gradska četvrt Trešnjevka - sjever], accessed 2011-08-06</ref> ** Including the neighbourhoods (''mjesni odbori'') of: [[Stara Trešnjevka]], [[Ljubljanica (Trešnjevka)|Ljubljanica]], [[Rudeš]], [[Voltino]], [[Pongračevo]] etc. * [[Trešnjevka - jug]] (''Trešnjevka - south'')<ref>[[City of Zagreb]], [http://www.zagreb.hr/default.aspx?id=156 Gradska četvrt Trešnjevka - jug], accessed 2011-08-06</ref> ** Including the neighbourhoods (''mjesni odbori'') of: [[Knežija]], [[Horvati (Trešnjevka)|Horvati]], [[Srednjaci]], [[Jarun]], [[Staglišće]], [[Gredice (Trešnjevka)|Gredice]], [[Vrbani, Zagreb|Vrbani]], [[Rudeš]] etc.
